				+activity("TechKobwa Girl's Computer Camp",'Camp Director and Creator ', 'images/techkobwa.jpg', 'Peace Corps Rwanda', '1/2013-8/2013', "TechKobwa is a one week computer camp for disadvantaged girls that I created during my time in Rwanda.")(class="well well-sm")
					:markdown
						Bringing TechKobwa to life involved coordinating many organizations, including [Girls in ICT Rwanda](https://www.facebook.com/GirlsInICTRW) and [kLab](http://klab.rw/).
						The curriculum was specially designed for the camp. It included
						lessons on programming using MIT's [Scratch](http://scratch.mit.edu/) 
						and a lesson from [Computer Science Unplugged](http://csunplugged.org/) where the whole camp collaborated
						to make a giant pixel-art [picture](images\techkobwa_pixels.jpg) of the mascot. [littleBits](http://littlebits.cc/) kindly donated  some of their awesome kits to the camp.
						TechKobwa will be continuing next year with support from [Michigan State University](http://www.cse.msu.edu/tc4g/) and IBM.

						**See**
						[State Department Article](http://iipdigital.usembassy.gov/st/english/article/2013/09/20130913282834.html#axzz2yWuQIeMk),
						[Rwandan New Times Article](http://www.newtimes.co.rw/news/views/article_print.php?15451&a=16286&week=32),
						[Photos](https://www.flickr.com/photos/celebdu/sets/72157635291190831/) 
						courtesy of [Mike Goren](http://www.mortalwombat.net/),
						[Gender and Development PC Rwanda blog post](http://gadpcrwanda.blogspot.com/2013/08/camp-techkobwa-by-liz-s_19.html),
						[Blog post by Elisabeth Turner](http://detourscenery.wordpress.com/2013/08/23/camp-techkobwa/).
				
				+activity("Gashora Girls Academy Computer Lab", 'Technology and Lab Manager', 'images/computerlab_kagame.jpg', 'Peace Corps Rwanda', '2011-2013', "Gashora Girls Academy has a sweet computer lab.")
					:markdown
						Gashora Girls Academy had a lot of technical needs during my time there. We were blessed with donated machines running
						[Windows Multipoint Server](http://www.microsoft.com/casestudies/Windows-Multipoint-Server-2011/Gashora-Girls-Academy/Rwandan-Girls-Academy-Models-Cost-EffectiveTechnology-Solution-for-Future-Schools/4000010078)
						and 270 [OLPC laptops](http://one.laptop.org/). I organized students to help administer the lab as student monitors
						and set up a <a href="#schooltool" data-id="schooltool" class="scroll-link">student database</a> 
						for the school using the open source SIS [SchoolTool](http://schooltool.org/).

						**See**
						[Computer Lab Policy Documents](media/GGAST Computer Lab Policy 2013.doc), [Student Monitor Video](http://youtu.be/_oFwRCOYCSM), [Easy Tomato Router Software](http://www.easytomato.org/)

