				+activity("SchoolTool Grade Gadget",'Programmed', 'images/schooltool.png', 'Gashora Girls Academy', '2011-2013', "My school needed a quick way to make report cards.")(id="schooltool" class="well well-sm")
					:markdown
						[Gashora Girls Academy](http://www.rwandagirlsinitiative.org/ggast/) was also looking for a student database. 
						I picked the open source SIS [SchoolTool](www.schooltool.org) and went to work creating a program that
						would allow administers to make printable reports from exported excel data. I wrote the Gashora Grade Gadget
						using Python 2.7. It generates an html document that can be fed in to [Prince](http://www.princexml.com/) to create beautiful printable
						PDFs. For the GUI, I used the [wx.Python](http://www.wxpython.org/) library and to create an executable I used
						[pyBuilder](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/PyBuilder-for-Py2exe/0.3).

						**See**
						[Code on GitHub](https://github.com/ceruleanotter/gradegadget), [Report Card Example](), [Midterm Report Example](), [GUI Screenshot]() 					
